Royal Valley Bands
September 7 at 7:50 PM ·

The RVHS Band is teaming up with the Sertoma Clubs of Topeka for the Great Topeka Duck Race!

Thousands of rubber ducks will be dropped into Lake Shawnee on Saturday, September 19th. If a duck you adopted is amongst the first to cross the finish line, then you win a prize! You don't have to be present to win. All duck adoptions are completed online.

Please consider supporting the band, as we will receive 50% of all money raised! https://www.duckrace.com/topeka/teams/10705
-

-
-
(A list of organizations the Sertoma club supports and the available PRIZES can be found at: https://www.duckrace.com/topeka)

Parents of Junior High and High School Football Campers,

The district became aware over the weekend that a camper at our August 3 - 7th football camp has tested positive for the COVID-19 virus. post_text: Need access? Check out the list
shared_text:
Aaric Davis
March 30 at 3:14 PM ·

Giant Communications has created FREE public WiFi access to the Internet in two locations within the district. The front drive and parking at Royal Valley Middle School and along Central Avenue behind Stithem Service Station in Hoyt. Look for the network titled: JBN/Giant - Keeping you Connected.

shared_text:
United Way of Greater Topeka
March 30 at 9:23 AM ·

Good luck to students and teachers today on your first day of virtual learning! Remember to pace yourself, exercise some patience, give yourself some grace, and take time to have fun! We know you've got this!

Feel free to leave an encouraging message below for our students and teachers across Shawnee, Jackson, and Jefferson Counties! #LiveUnited
